  "instructions": {
    "L": [
      { "S": "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and lightly spray with olive or avocado oil." },
      { "S": "Process the aromatics in a food processor by pulsing the 2 tablespoons parsley, 2 tablespoons cilantro, 4 baby carrots, 1 scallion (cut into pieces), and 1 clove garlic until finely chopped, scraping down the sides as needed." },
      { "S": "Add the remaining falafel ingredients to the food processor: drained and rinsed chickpeas, 2 tablespoons chickpea flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1 1/2 tablespoons olive oil, 1 tablespoon lemon juice, 1 tablespoon hemp seeds, 1/2 tablespoon chia seeds, 1 teaspoon ground flax seeds, and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Pulse until well combined but still textured — do NOT purée into a smooth paste." },
      { "S": "Rest the falafel mixture for 5 minutes to allow the chia and flax seeds to absorb moisture and act as binders." },
      { "S": "Shape the mixture using a spoon or small cookie scoop (about 2 tablespoons each) to form approximately 9 balls, then gently flatten into thick patties about 3/4 inch thick. Place on the prepared baking sheet." },
      { "S": "Spray the tops of the falafels lightly with olive or avocado oil spray for crispiness." },
      { "S": "Bake at 375°F for 15 minutes. Flip carefully, spray again lightly, and bake for an additional 12-15 minutes until golden brown and crispy on the outside." },
      { "S": "Make the herbed yogurt sauce by stirring together 1 cup Greek yogurt, 3-4 teaspoons lemon juice, 1 1/2 tablespoons chopped dill, 1 clove minced garlic, 1 tablespoon chopped parsley, and a pinch of salt in a small bowl. Taste and adjust seasonings as desired. Refrigerate until ready to serve." },
      { "S": "Divide the mixed greens among 3 bowls. Top each with cucumbers, cherry tomatoes, red onion, kalamata olives, and feta cheese." },
