      { "S": "Heat a Dutch oven or large soup pot over medium-high heat. Add 1 lb ground beef and 1/2 lb ground sausage. Season lightly with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking the meat into small pieces with a wooden spoon, until well browned, about 6-8 minutes. Drain excess fat if needed." },
      { "S": "Add 1 chopped large yellow onion and cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 minutes until slightly softened. Add 4 minced garlic cloves and stir for 30 seconds until fragrant (don't let it burn). Add 2 quartered and sliced carrots and 5 cups chopped cabbage and cook for 2 minutes, stirring to combine." },
      { "S": "Add 5 cups beef broth, 2 cans tomato sauce, 1 can diced tomatoes with their juices, 1 Tablespoon Worcestershire sauce, 1 1/2 teaspoons smoked paprika, 1 teaspoon oregano, 1/2 teaspoon thyme, and 1 bay leaf. Stir well and bring to a boil. Stir in 3/4 cup dry rice." },
      { "S": "Reduce heat to low, cover the pot, and simmer for 25-30 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking, until the rice is tender and the cabbage is soft. If the soup looks too thick, stir in the remaining 1 cup of beef broth or more to your preference." },
      { "S": "Remove bay leaf. Stir in lemon juice (about 1 Tablespoon) and 2 Tablespoons fresh parsley. Taste and season with additional salt and pepper as needed. Ladle into bowls and serve hot." }
