      {"S": "Heat 1 Tablespoon olive oil over medium-high heat in a Dutch oven or large stockpot. Add 1 pound ground turkey and cook, breaking it into small pieces with a wooden spoon, until cooked through and no pink remains (about 5-7 minutes). Remove turkey from the pot and set aside on a plate. Drain any excess liquid from the pot."},
      {"S": "Add the remaining 2 Tablespoons olive oil to the pot. Once the oil is hot and shimmering, add 1 diced onion, 3 diced celery ribs, 1/2 diced poblano pepper, and 1 shredded carrot. Cook for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally, then add 3 minced garlic cloves and cook 1 minute more until fragrant."},
      {"S": "Meanwhile, whisk together 1/2 cup masa harina, 1 Tablespoon cumin, 1 Tablespoon garlic powder, 1 Tablespoon kosher salt, 2 teaspoons chili powder, 2 teaspoons ancho chili powder, 1 1/2 teaspoons paprika, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, and 1/2 teaspoon coriander in a small bowl."},
      {"S": "Return the cooked turkey to the pot. Sprinkle the spice-masa mixture evenly over the turkey and vegetables. Stir well and cook for 1-2 minutes to toast the spices and allow the masa harina to begin absorbing moisture."},
      {"S": "Add 2 cups chicken broth, 2 cans diced tomatoes with green chilies (with their juices), drained kidney beans, drained black beans, and creamed corn. Stir thoroughly to combine, making sure to scrape up any browned bits from the bottom of the pot."},
